    <item>
      <title>How to Start a Flask Project Using Visual Studio Code</title>
      <link>/post/how-to-start-a-flask-project-using-visual-studio/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 02 Sep 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>/post/how-to-start-a-flask-project-using-visual-studio/</guid>
      <description>
        
          &lt;img src=&#34;/img/how-to-start-a-flask-project-using-visual-studio-0.png&#34;/&gt;
          
        
        
        
          Flask is a Python web micro-framework. “Micro” because it doesn’t require any particular tools or libraries. Flask main objective is to keep a simple but extensible core. There is no database abstraction feature, no authentication, no cookie manager … because a lot of extensions already did it well !
So, at the opposite of an all-in-one framework such as Django, you can do whatever you want with Flask but nothing more.
          
        
        </description>
